# Go build artifacts — compiled binaries must NOT be committed.
# Both used to live next to the source at 9MB each, doubling repo size on every
# rebuild. CI now builds them on-demand. Post-#H5 the entry point is at
# cmd/server/. Three binary names are covered:
#   - cmd/server/server: produced by `go build ./cmd/server` run inside cmd/server
#   - src/services/go-engine/server: produced by `go build ./cmd/server` run
#     from the module root (Go writes the binary to CWD, not the package dir)
#   - legacy names (go-engine, iqra-engine, engine) kept for old branches
/src/services/go-engine/server
/src/services/go-engine/go-engine
/src/services/go-engine/iqra-engine
/src/services/go-engine/engine
/src/services/go-engine/cmd/server/server
/src/services/go-engine/cmd/server/go-engine
/src/services/go-engine/*.exe
/src/services/go-engine/*.test
/src/services/go-engine/cmd/server/*.exe
/src/services/go-engine/cmd/server/*.test
*.exe
